		"name": "Blockchain Network — EVM Service",
		"description": "HTTP API for the single-chain EVM microservice (`evm.js`).\n\n**Setup:** Copy `.env.example` to `.env`, set `EVM_RPC_URL`, `EVM_PAID_RPC_URL`, `EVM_CHAIN_ID`, `EVM_PORT`, then run `npm start`.\n\n**Base URL:** Default `http://localhost:5000/api` (collection variable `base_url`).\n\n**Responses:** Most endpoints return JSON objects on success or the literal `false` on failure (HTTP 200).\n\n**History endpoints** require `EVM_PAID_RPC_URL`. Block scans are limited by `EVM_MAX_BLOCK_RANGE` (default 2000).\n\n**Security:** Send endpoints accept private keys in the body — use only on trusted networks.",
		"schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
	},
